eligibility_criteria.description:
Minimum age: 20 Years
Maximum age: 60 Years

Patients with unresected squamous cell cancer (SCC) arising in the oral cavity, oropharynx, larynx, or hypopharynx are excluded, unless they have received at least 2 cycles of induction chemotherapy with a regimen that includes cisplatin or carboplatin
Able to converse, write and read English

groups.description: Patients receive Akt inhibitor MK2206 PO on days -9 and -2, and undergo segmental resection or total mastectomy (therapeutic conventional surgery) on day 0. Patient samples will be processed for pharmacological study and laboratory biomarker analysis.

interventions.name: Drug, Food, Chemical or Biomedical Material

groups.name: Treatment (Akt inhibitor MK2206)

outcome_measures.analysis_method: The proportion of disagreements across all time points will be estimated with an intercept-only GEE regression model that accounts for correlation among measures from the same patient. This proportion will be reported with a 95% confidence interval.
outcome_measures.measure: Frequency with which CT and qualitative FDG-PET disagree in their classifications of response

outcome_measures.analysis_method: Will be assessed by comparisons using analysis of variance followed by paired t-test or other tests (Wilcoxon rank-sum test), if normality assumption is not satisfied even when data transformation is performed.
outcome_measures.measure: Change in Th1, Th2, and various immune regulatory cell populations in PBMC and assessed by flow cytometry

outcome_measures.analysis_method: Analgesic use will be tabulated, converted into equivalent units, and changes in opiate equivalents before and after treatment will be compared.
outcome_measures.measure: Change in analgesic use assessed by the WHO analgesic ladder
EFS between VHR T-LLy patients treated with HR BFM intensification blocks who have partial remission or complete remission with those who do not respond
